tler:...` to `gitbutler:...` needs a bulk prefix-rename or\n-atomic set-and-remove primitive, fix that in `[REDACTED:path]` rather\n-than papering over it downstream.\n+Publishing should be implemented as a careful metadata move, not a hacky\n+read/write/delete workaround. Since `local:` keys are not serialized, moving them\n+inside the local database should be cheap in principle, but that needs to be\n+verified against the actual `git-meta-lib` API and storage model.\n+\n+If the needed rename/move primitive is generic enough, it should probably live in\n+`[REDACTED:path]`. If it turns out to be agentlog-specific, keep it in\n+`but-agentlog`. Make that call during implementation; do not build fake\n+extensibility just to avoid the decision.\n+\n+Prefer the simplest correct path. No broad policy engine, no generic migration\n+framework, and no clever abstraction unless the code demands it.\n@@\n ## Open Questions\n \n-- Should `publish` move local data or copy it and leave a local copy behind? Move\n-  still looks like the right default, but implementation may uncover a reason to\n-  keep local copies.\n-- What exact `gitbutler.*` config key should control per-repo share-by-default?\n-- Does `git-meta-lib` need an atomic `MetaEdit::Remove` or prefix-move API before\n-  this is pleasant and safe to implement?\n+- Where should the local-to-published key move live: upstream in `git-meta-lib`\n+  as a generic primitive, or locally in `but-agentlog` as agentlog-specific\n+  behavior?\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-31T12:20:09.936Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}